dal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533326\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533326\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wez1665702679109.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wez1665702679109.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wez1665702679109.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wez1665702679109\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define Operation Parameters in a Signature\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Parameters enable you to pass information in and out of operations. For Uniface components, you can define parameters by entering ProcScript in the appropriate operation or trigger. When integrating non-Uniface components, you can define parameters in the component signature using the Signature Editor.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"wez1665702679109__context_w3401ab1b5b1_w3402ab1b5_w3403ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"wez1665702679109__topic_d34088e1_d34089e1_d34090e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wez1665702679109__p_d34091e1_d34092e1_d34093e1\">When you define parameters for a method or operation, the list of parameters must match the number, type, and order of arguments for the operation as used in the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> statement.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wez1665702679109__p_d34094e1_d34095e1_d34096e1\">To define or edit the parameters of component implementations:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17468e1_d17469e1_d17470e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To create a new parameter, in the Signature Editor:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17471e1_d17472e1_d17473e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">+</span> button beside the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Parameter</span> fields.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17474e1_d17475e1_d17476e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Enter a name and select or clear the In and Out check boxes as required.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17477e1_d17478e1_d17479e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wez1665702679109__p_d34097e1_d34098e1_d34099e1\">To edit a parameter, select it in the Sand click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span> adjacent to the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Parameter</span> fields.\n The Define Parameter form is displayed.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"wez1665702679109__note_w3404ab1b5b3b3b3b1_w3405ab1b5b3b3b3_w3406ab1b5b3b3_w3407ab1b5b3_w3408ab1b5_w3409ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You cannot define parameters for the <code class=\"ph codeph\">ACCEPT</code> or\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">QUIT</code> operations.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17480e1_d17481e1_d17482e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wez1665702679109__p_d34100e1_d34101e1_d34102e1\">Select an existing parameter or click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span> and enter the parameter name in the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Name</span> field. If the parameter is used in an\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> statement, the parameter name can be a component\n               variable, string, field, or entity.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17483e1_d17484e1_d17485e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data Type</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Direction</span> properties.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17486e1_d17487e1_d17488e1\">If the parameter is a field, component variable, or string, select <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Basic</span> and select a Uniface data type from the list.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17489e1_d17490e1_d17491e1\">if the parameter is an entity parameter or occurrence, select <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Entity</span> or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Occurrence</span> and enter or select the name of an analyzed application entity. For restrictions on these data types, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bbz1665702679178.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bbz1665702679178.html\" title=\"Name of the Entity to use if the parameter's data type is Entity or Occurrence.\">Corresponding Model and Entity Name</a>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"wez1665702679109__note_jy1_x52_2cc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> To setup C implementation data types properties, see\n                     <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"znk1721892868055.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/znk1721892868055.html\" title=\"C implementation data types properties explanation.\">C Implementation Data Types Properties</a>.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17492e1_d17493e1_d17494e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wez1665702679109__p_d34103e1_d34104e1_d34105e1\">Select the required implementation from the list and specify the following attributes:\n If you created a new parameter, Uniface generates the default name <var class=\"keyword varname\">ComponentName_ParameterName</var>to ensure that it is unique.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17495e1_d17496e1_d17497e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wnv1665702679250.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wnv1665702679250.html\" title=\"Case-sensitive name of the parameter, up to 32 characters. All NLS characters are valid, but the first character must be a letter. Uniface maps its (uppercase) signature parameter name to this one.\">Literal Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17498e1_d17499e1_d17500e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rvv1665702679319.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rvv1665702679319.html\" title=\"Data interface for this parameter. The available choices depend on the implementation and the data type.\">Interface</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17501e1_d17502e1_d17503e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jxy1665702679389.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jxy1665702679389.html\" title=\"Length of the parameter string. The value can be from 1 to 2147483647, depending on the data type.\">Length</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17504e1_d17505e1_d17506e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uqj1665702679458.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uqj1665702679458.html\" title=\"Number of occurrences allowed. For parameters of type entity or occurrence, you can specify a fixed number of occurrences from 1 through 2147483647.\">No. of Occurrences</a> —use only for entity and occurrence parameters\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wez1665702679109__li_d17507e1_d17508e1_d17509e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To delete a parameter from the signature, in the Define Parameter form, select the operation you want to delete and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete</span>.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tpe1665702530336.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>params…endparams</a><p>Declare the parameter block for an operation, function, or global ProcScript.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533326\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533326\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Operation Parameters in a Signature Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Operation Parameters in a Signature Parameters enable you to pass information in and out of operations. For Uniface components, you can define parameters by entering ProcScript in the appropriate operation or trigger. When integrating non-Uniface components, you can define parameters in the component signature using the Signature Editor. When you define parameters for a method or operation, the list of parameters must match the number, type, and order of arguments for the operation as used in the activate statement. To define or edit the parameters of component implementations: To create a new parameter, in the Signature Editor: Click the + button beside the Parameter fields. Enter a name and select or clear the In and Out check boxes as required. To edit a parameter, select it in the Sand click >> adjacent to the Parameter fields. The Define Parameter form is displayed. Note: You cannot define parameters for the ACCEPT or QUIT operations. Select an existing parameter or click New and enter the parameter name in the Name field. If the parameter is used in an activate statement, the parameter name can be a component variable, string, field, or entity. Set the Data Type and Direction properties. If the parameter is a field, component variable, or string, select Basic and select a Uniface data type from the list. if the parameter is an entity parameter or occurrence, select Entity or Occurrence and enter or select the name of an analyzed application entity. For restrictions on these data types, see Corresponding Model and Entity Name . Note: To setup C implementation data types properties, see C Implementation Data Types Properties . Select the required implementation from the list and specify the following attributes: If you created a new parameter, Uniface generates the default name ComponentName_ParameterName to ensure that it is unique. Literal Name Interface Length No. of Occurrences —use only for entity and occurrence parameters To delete a parameter from the signature, in the Define Parameter form, select the operation you want to delete and click Delete . Related Links params…endparams Declare the parameter block for an operation, function, or global ProcScript. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}